        <p><strong>Response functions</strong> are mathematical relationships between fire characteristic (e.g., flame length) and fire outcome. In other words, response functions describe the effect of fire on the values at risk. There are 14 pre-defined response functions, which are described in the <MadCap:xref href="../../06-Risk-Assessment/RiskAssessResponseFunctions.htm"><strong>Response Functions Table</strong></MadCap:xref>.</p>
